  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

11:30 AM DA calls cases 21CM91 and 22CM15 and states appearances. Defendant Kelsey N.M. Hauk appeared in court. Karl J. Kelz appeared for the State of Wisconsin. DA Kelz states case 22CM15 is set for Plea and Sentencing and case 21cm91 is set for a status hearing. Defendant states she wants to accept the offer in case 21CM91 as well today and be sentenced on both. DA Kelz recites the offer for case 21CM91. Defendant agrees to the offers in both cases. In case 21CM91 contingent upon the defendan't plea to Ct. 2 the State will move to Dismiss and read in Ct. 1 and will allow expunction in this case after successful completion of probation. Court explains to defedant and DA that in a case with a charge that is dismissed and read in the case would not be able to be expunged. Defendant questions the court. Court gives responses to defendant's questions regarding expunction. DA Kelz makes statements to defendant. Defendant states she will accept the plea deal in case 22CM15 and wait for appointment of Attorney in case 21CM91. Comments by the court. Defendant wishes to withdraw her previous plea and adjourn this hearing in order to obtain counsel before proceeding.   Court orders Pre-trial conference be scheduled for 05/24/2022 at 4:00 PM. Defendant inquires about a Petition for Court Appointed Attorney she had filed with the court. Court makes comments and denies the Appointment at this time due to financials. Defendant will resubmit a new Petition with most current financials included.
